MAMBA NOTES:
Intro: Faster version of Conda, dependency resolution and parallel downloading - significantly speed up package installation and environment management 
Install: Have installed. One method of doing so is:
conda install mamba -n base -c conda-forge
Look up for more info:
https://mamba.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installation/mamba-installation.html
Basic Commands:
- install: mamba install <package-name>
- create environment: mamba create -n <env-name> <package-list>
- activate environment: mamba activate <env-name>
- deactivate environment: mamba deactivate
- list installed environments: mamba env list
- create environments from YAML files (?): mamba env create -f environment.yml
- adding conda channels: mamba config --add channels <channel-name>
- view active channels: mamba config --show channels
- remove package: mamba remove <package-name>
- update package: mamba update <package-name>
- search package: mamba search <package-name>
- repoquery search: mamba repoquery search <package-name>
- repoquery dependencies: mamba repoquery depends <package-name>

